article.description: — Javon Greene scored 19 points and South Florida cruised to a 75-51 victory over Central Florida on Saturday night.
article.headline: South Florida cruises past Central Florida 75-51
article.linkText: South Florida cruises past Central Florida 75-51
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. -- — Javon Greene scored 19 points and South Florida cruised to a 75-51 victory over Central Florida on Saturday night. Greene shot 7 of 12 from the floor, made five 3-pointers and had nine rebounds. Caleb Murphy added 13 points for South Florida (6-10, 1/3 American Athletic Conference). Jamir Chaplin added 10 points. C.J. Walker had nine points to lead Central Florida (10-5, 2-3), which shot 19 of 57 (33%) overall and missed 18 of 20 3-point attempts. Central Florida plays at East Carolina on Tuesday. South Florida plays at No. 11 Houston on Tuesday. ------
